reviews.text: WOW WOW WOW.  we where out of town and wanted somewhere to brunch and the first thing that caught our eye was the silver diner.  We were waited on by Arthur! If you guys wants AMAZING service. Go see Arthur! He was superb with our first experience. He went above and beyond.  He catered to the needs of my daughters and was kind enough to replace a meal that was missing something.  This man deserves an award! If you’re reading this Arthur, keep being you.  Keep making a difference in the lives of others. Management if your reading this.  Give this man a raise! 👏🏼👏🏼
The service was great and food came out quick. We ordered the red, white, and blue french toast, meatless taco bowl, and the shrimp and watermelon salad. Everything was very fresh and delicious!

Classic diner atmosphere with healthier, cleaner, fresher food! Had the Bay Benedict, which came with crab cake and fresh fruit. Boyfriend had Philly cheesesteak omelet, and we shared pancakes with real syrup. All perfect. Tea came in a huge mug with real honey on the side. Great service. Felt good and not heavy/greasy afterward. Operational jukebox machines at each table

Food is always delicious and their presentation is always top notch. I highly recommend their Stuffed French Toast and if your looking for a delicious desert their Home-Style Breaded Pudding is to die for! It's like food for the soul eat bite just makes you want to siiiiiiiiinggg!!!😁
Great diner food with fast and quick service. Enjoyed breakfast listening to some old tunes on the Jukebox while enjoying a mimosa. Definitely would go back when in the area.
I come to the Subway at Greenway in Greenbelt frequently and have mostly good experiences with the servers and the food. I intend to continue going here as it's one of my favorite local restaurants.

This is the worst subway I ordered a salad and the amount that I received was not sufficient I asked for my money back and the manager told me it was not her fault and she is not giving me my money back and she will not make me a new salad. The young lady how help me was very nice but the “manager “ Kamala needs to be retrained she is extremely unprofessional

I gave one star because I had to just to leave a review. Customer service skills are terrible. There is one guy that is always rude NO matter what. He is tall, glasses and has dark hair. He likes to roll his eyes and act like I am disturbing him. Plus they forgot my cookies I tried to call them and they NEVER answered. Where is the customer service?? We won't be back at all.
Excellent service. There is a lady name  Wendy. She makes very delicious sandwiches. 😋
They gave me rotten chicken in my wrap. I open it and smelled it from away. Stay away from this location

Had dinner with my family here the other night. We’re new to the area and we’re looking for a place to eat. Delicious food. Great service. Very good portions for the price. Will definitely be a regular here.

Customer service is amazing, all the workers there are very kind and polite. The food is amazing my favorite thing on the menu is either the pizza or the Philly cheesesteak. As you can see I couldn’t wait to take a bite.

I've been going here for over 20 years. Best pizza and subs and the price is very reasonable. Owner is great guy. Definitely recommend if you're in college park area. My favorite things are meat lovers pizza and steak and cheese and hot cut subs. You won't be disappointed.

We’ve been coming here for well over a decade. Some of the best value food. When we need something quick and decent, this is the place. We love the Italian hot cut, cold Turkey sub, hot wings, and meat lover pizza

Good neighborhood pizzeria. If you live close and enough and are willing to call for delivery, your pizza will arrive hot. The pizza can be a bit inconsistent with regards to the amount of sauce and cheese, sometimes I find it too cheesy for me. The salads are also good, although a bit heavy on the white onion for a salad.

These restaurants are a bargain across the board. Tasty fresh food of the Mexican cuisine.  Fair prices. Drinks and condiments.  While the interior is bare bones with concrete floors you save money there. Adequate and clean interiors with the added luxury that is a fast (assembly line) cheap, fairly healthy, very tasty with a great carry out service.

This location is going downhill. The food is inconsistent never tastes the same. Now it’s almost always it doesn’t taste good. Ive tried going during the day when it’s not as crowded and it makes no difference. This location is always understaffed. Last time I ate here,  it was terrible and my food was cold. The beans were not cooked and tasted like they came from a can.  The steak was chewy and not cooked well. The food lacks flavor and seasoning.

I’m going back to Cava and Seoul Spice!!! Also don’t order online or use delivery apps here the order is never right.

Juice drinks were almost empty. This isn't the first time I ordered a large drink and there wasn't enough to fill the cup. They should be monitored and refilled more frequently as needed based on the amount of customers this location serves. Otherwise, everything else was good.

They were under staffed it appeared and tables were all dirty. My burrito was thrown together rice and beans at bottom and cheese and meat and lettice at the top. Nothing had any flavor like the 1 on Annapolis road. It's always perfect store is always clean food is fresh and tasteful.  I did want to commend the young man who was busier than the other employees and was working his hardest by his self to get line down while other employees were meeting and mingling in the dining room back and forth. He was very tired and needed some team work. And I felt since he was the only African American in the restaurant he felt alone. Praying for diversity in there shifts and schedules and in the team players to work together as a team and to rotate positions when they are busy. I was there between 230-330 !!

I ordered food from the Chipotle mobile app at 6:09pm. The order was to be ready at 6:20pm, I got there at 6:17pm and did not get my order until 6:44pm. Just let that sink in, the operations of this store is garbage. The workers are overworked because of the way they work, unorganized. Don’t get food or order from this area, unless you like an hour wait. Just shut this one down and fire the workers, order at the Beltsville location.

The staff was a little slow, but very nice.  The coffee was stronger the an usual but it served is purpose of keeping me awake.  I stopped by this location because I happened to be in College Park.  I'm not sure I would make this my go to store but if I'm in the area again,  I would consider stopping, but I would not recommend this particular location.

Just stopped by and walked out.  The two guys working there...one was casually speaking with this lady.  Neither of them greeted or acknowledged me.  I just walked out and left. Never been here before, and won't be back.  I work in the service industry so all they had to do is say to give them a sec and they'll be right with me

Safe to say I am never coming back here. The lady at the register was rude, inpatient with customer orders, slow, messed up the entire order, and forgot some of the things that come with the order. She really knows how to mess up your morning with that attitude. Felt bad for the one lady who was actually doing her job  in the back who had to deal with that.

Nothing but bad experiences from this dunkin donuts. My most recent and final visit, i placed a mobile order for a drink and a 6 pack of donuts. I took a while to arrive, turns out they hadn't made my box, so most of the donuts i chose were gone. The workers are incompetent and rude. The location is in an awkward spot anyways, you can only make a right turn to enter and exit.

They don't listen at all ...their stingy with Carmel and think u dnt know their putting vanilla icecream in ur cap blast when u order sothing else . Be watery and even if u ask for extra Carmel u not getting it employees act like they have additude to fix ur order
The food was good but they tear off the part of the receipt that has a coupon on it.

I placed an online order and when I arrived my order wasn’t in there system. I waited about 10 minutes and my order still wasn’t showing up so I placed another order using a different card. Both orders mysteriously popped up about 5 minutes after that so I asked the older white lady with the short haircut to cancel one order and she did NOT which I believe she did on purpose because she had a snarky attitude with customers the entire time I was there! Always ask for voided receipts!

The chicken was hard and tasted like it was spoiled before it was cooked. Would have taken it back if I lived closer instead of throwing it in the trash.
Will  not order from Greenbelt  restaurant ever again!

A friend of mine payed for my food for me and when I go to check a female employee called me a liar and insulted me because of my race. She has banned me from the establishment for no reason and threatened to call the police on me. Racist workers at this place

A female employee threatened my son by saying the establishment will call the police  for no reason. A friend of his payed for food for him but they called us a layers and more.    Very stressful experience

I really like this station, mainly because the GSTV at the pumps is muted.

I am changing rating to 5 stars after update the next day, because:

I just spoke with a Maryland Comptroller field enforcement agent, and I am satisfied.

The station offered to refund the difference and I declined. I just want them to be careful in the future, and that will be sufficient resolution for me.
---

DO NOT TRUST THEIR POSTED PRICE. This morning the big lit sign had $5.129 / gallon for premium, but the pump was set to $5.299. The attendant said they could not turn off the sign.
They overcharged me $2.65 on 15.58 gallons as seen in photo attached.
If people didn't hang out there so much it would be a decent gas station..
They have great customer services.
I spent 70 dollars on gas and their restroom is “not working” even though I saw someone use it.
this shell gas station jacks up there prices for example a package of $0.99 cent Game Wraps they sell for a 1.49 before taxes when the package is clearly marked $0 .99.

I know there's many places to have Peruvian style rotisserie chicken. Not sure why this is different, a spice or time the chicken is marinated. This is probably the best chicken I've had. Most other places are heavy of the smoky flavor. This has very minimal smoky taste which I prefer. They have many side option. I just opted to have chicken alone without sides.

I got nachos with steak. Now I thought the steak would be more strip cuts. It was more small diced morsels. Lots of cheese. Something different I never had on nachos was cooked mild peppers like fajitas but diced. Also added corn. Though I couldnt finish the nachos-overall enjoyed the chicken and nachos!
Stopped here on a whim for lunch and got the pollo saltado. Nice portion size, and pretty good flavor. The staff was friendly and it feels like a nice little slice of Latino culture.

Terrible worker. I came in for the Wednesday special when a young middle eastern man attempted to take out the half chicken special price off when I was looking away. I will never trust this restaurant again. Can’t deal with crooks.
The food is always on point love everything i tried especially the cheesy potatoes and the steak burrito and the chicken with the yellow sauce
Food is delicious. The best chicken i've had in a while at a Peruvian resturante or carry out.  Go there you will love it.

They gave me spoiled fried rice and a severe tummy ache! They tried to hide the spoiled taste by putting a bunch of teriyaki sauce but the flavor of spoiled rice is still there. I don’t know how anyone can serve rotten food!

Update: threw up the entire night. They refunded me but they were not apologetic at all. No sorry, nothing. AVOID THIS PLACE
Had the shrimp and chicken with rice and noodles yesterday. It was soo good that I reordered it today but with steak this time. Great food!
Clean place! Great stuff! Fast service! And food is great!

I have never really been a fan of chicken teriyaki until now. Food is amazing and wait time is between 5-10 minutes depending how full it is. Value is also exceptionally good for the quality of the food.

Did they change management?  The food has barely have any taste now.    My food was chicken and shrimp teriyaki with noodles and veggies. No matter how much sauce was added it's like watered down to NO FLAVOR.

Great subs at good prices ($16 ish for a giant (1400-1800 calories)), options for customizations and tons of predesigned classics. Service is pretty quick and there is ample indoor seating. Convenient location at Beltway Plaza mall. They also have chips and sodas. Ample indoor seating and they also have a restroom.

We got the chicken bacon ranch (very good) and the Mike's Phillycheese steak (good but not a great representation of the original Philadelphia one).

This restaurant has greatly improved.  They cut the ham and turkey cold cuts right off the block when I was here.  The sandwiches were fresh and tasty.  Chipotle steak and cheese made my son very happy.  Food was good!  Service was very professional and quick.  Bathrooms are available and clean.  Was refreshing seeing the manager really applying his skill to the business and seemed to take pride in it.  Hope it lasts!

World Class customer service!!! The store is very clean and you can see them.make your sandwich. I got two regular sandwiches for $20.00 a cold club supreme and hot steak and cheese. The steak and cheese was very good.
My go to. I recently had to become Gluten Free due to food allergies and health issues. Jersey Mike's is always so careful to keep my sub GF and fresh. Great  place to eat.
They need to practice better food safety. Keep talking over food while preparing. Need to cover mouths with masks. Other than that, they are friendly and the establishment is clean

This is a good place to get BBQ quickly and relatively inexpensive. The moist brisket was really good and the burnt ends were delicious. Some parts of the brisket were cut thick but the flavor was good. The sides are very good. The Mac and cheese is old fashioned and has a great flavor. The cheesy potatoes were a welcomed surprise. They were creamy and very cheesy. Personally my favorite side. Overall we enjoy this place and would definitely go back.

Searched em up on Google Maps. We are from out of town.

Meats were GREAT. Awesome smoky flavor. Sides were really good. And the Naner Pudding is off the chain!!!

Military themed joint. Will go again if I get the chance!!
Yummy!!! Haven’t had a crazy amount of bbq in my lifetime but this was the best pulled pork sandwich I’ve ever had. Really loved the restaurant decor and environment too.

The restaurant was very clean as usual. The staff was friendly and the service was fast. Now to the food that's what we're all really here for. Brisket, good not better than mine but good none the less. Wifey got the pulled chicken juicy not dry is always good. We got the collard greens. Didn't realize it came with tomatoes in the mix. Two ingredients you don't usually see together but it worked!. The Mac and cheese was NOT up to par. The Mac and cheese has been hit or miss here since the beginning. Just depends on who makes the batch you get. Was pretty much just really dry and under seasoned. Also got the shrimp. That was good as well.

Outstanding BBQ, everything tastes superb!
Got the XXL combo with turkey and collard greens and green beans and it was some of the best BBQ I've had. Even the bbq sauces were amazing. Highly recommend this restaurant.

This is another place me and da hubby love to come since the first day we came. If you a Pizza lover, pasta lover or Italian food lover you can't go wrong wit this place. I love that's in a mall setting so you can shop and eat good. They also have a bar for drink cotails only beer and wine to slow da edge of dealing wit kids or family all dam day💁🏽‍♀️ bar food and seafood. If your ever in Greenbelt check this place out. I guarantee u will love it. Service is amazing and very welcomeing. Our favorite is the Chesapeake Pasta. Make my stomach sing its so delicious 🤤

Great Italian food at a great price. Had the chicken parm and it was excellent. Entree, salad, and garlic bread for $16, you can’t beat it. Really nice service too. Its nice to see some places are still trying to deliver quality service and food at a reasonable price point.

Placed a take out order. Got hot subs: chicken Parmesan and steak and cheese; got some pasta dishes: Fettuccine Alfredo, lasagna and fries. Hard to find this place. You must drive around to the back and park in the parking garage area. Food was hot and good. Will be back.

This place has been a staple in Greenbelt MD. for years. Their food is consistently good and delicious. They have a casual and family friendly atmosphere. Whether you get pizza, sub, salad, stromboli or pasta, it's all good.

If you are truly looking for the best pizza around head to 3 Brothers! I'm not just saying it but I mean it. The atmosphere the food they even have tvs on to different channels for those family lovers 😁. The pepperoni and sausage extra cheese is the way to go in my opinion wish could give more stars.

It’s places like this that makes me feel they are a stable in the neighborhood and community. The food is delicious— kitchen opens until store closes. Their hot bar is a must— the pork spare ribs are to die for. My favorite is their lengua tacos. They also have a meat section as well as a small produce area. Support family owned small businesses and shop small here!

Worst service ever experience in my life.  Was looking for a place to take my students from college and introduce them to our foods, but this place its not one of them. Dont even deserve one star.  Lost many customers
Pupusa are good ,the Tamales are okay, price wise things are little higher.

The restaurant part of this place is ok. Pupusas are good and well priced. This place gets 3 starts because of the market part of the establishment. First occasion, my husband bought some hard cheese from here just to come home and realize the cheese had gone bad(This was back in the summer of 2020). The second occasion was a family member who went to buy a pack of hand made tortillas.
The ones on top were fine but once he got towards the ones in the middle, those ended up being slimy(this happened a few months back).
My advice: be careful of what you purchase if it’s coming from the store. The restaurant is fine.

Good and tasty food. Like several confirmed here... the pupusas was delicious and well priced. I also got the chicken platter with 2 sides. I only got 2 drumsticks though. For the price I paid I thought it was very expensive. I will give them another chance in the near future. And hope will get more chicken next time. I like the mom and pop shop.

DISGUSTING- I went there today and ordered the reuben sandwich..It LOOKS JUST LIKE IT TASTE! YUCK! I took a bite and it's disgusting, the meat is old, hard disgusting and I don't think it's reuben, the sauerkraft is old and disgusting, the bread is stale and disgusting, the cheese is old and disgusting..the place is old and dirty..I gave them a chance because someone said the reuben was good, THIS IS A LIE! I will never ever come back here again. They needed to be reported for selling this nasty old meat....I ADVISE U RUN FAR AWAY UNLESS U WANT TO GET SICK OR WASTE YOUR MONEY!

Have ordered delivery and dined in many times. These are good sandwiches for the price, made by people who care. The delivery fees have gotten to be a bit much given that we live about a half mile away. The dining room is definitely worn out, but clean enough to eat a sandwich in. They haven't always had what we wanted in stock, but they are also willing to accommodate just about any request they can. Far, far better than the chain sandwich shops.

First time going. Result,,,,3more times.Even after Thanksgiving.  Can't beat the quality and quantity. Not expensive either. Lots of variety also. I wish I could go more often. Will be returning after the holidays to eat even more menu items that I haven't tried yet. Thanks.
I love this little spot. I get a turkey reuben, and it's delicious. Make sure you stop and try here!

The service is always pleasant & great.  The food was on point & fast.  I always call ahead & order my food.  No waiting in line. Walk in, check my food tap that Google pay & I'm out the door with a smile. 😁
I order ahead of time, and honestly think their pizza is good.  It's always hot when I get it.
Well… the pizza is under cooked. The dough isn’t taste good and just like a chewing gum.  I wouldn’t recommend. 🤢🤮
I just called them to place an order and the young gentleman picks up the phone and says hello and thats it. I said is this Little Caesars he says yeah. Really
Could have been better for a 13.00 pizza 🍕 too thin and tge sauce a little spicy.

I've gotten pizzas from different restaurants but my parents always prefer Little Caesars. This location has the perfect thickness for their crust. I have only been let down once which was when I ordered an extramostbestest sausage and got paltry amount of the topping. All my other times the orders have been great. They are fast with orders and the store is clean. Plus that the employees are still wearing masks. Get the stuffed crust.

I ordered broccoli with brown sauce and general Tso chicken. The broccoli was delicious but I took a bite of the chicken and it tasted funny. So I took a closer look, all I have to say is IT DIDN'T LOOK LIKE chicken when I cut into the pieces, so I threw it out. For it to cost $20 and come to me looking the way it did, I am disappointed.

Delivery was fast and the crab rangoons were good. Problem was the kung pao chicken tasted and looked nothing like typical kung pao chicken. It wasn't spicy and it was very reminiscent of a type of "chicken with mixed vegetables dish" or "hunan chicken" with a garlicy type sauce with just some peanuts thrown in. I also was informed that chow mein is not in fact stir-fried noodles but instead vegetables and pork. It's sad that they got two staples from typical chinese restaurants wrong.

I have been coming here for years due to the convenience of it being in walking distance from my apartment. The service here is subpar and getting worse every time I come. the food food is average again I only eat from here every once and while due to how easy it is for me to pick up. The issue I have is with the prices I purchased a cheese burger totaling to just a little below $8 for a single cheese burger I wanted a extra slice of cheese and my jaw dropped when I was told that that would a extra $1.25 knowing they use the cheapest sliced cheese so I passed on that knowing I got some at home. When I arrived home and started to eat the food was terrible. The prices at this location keep going up the service keeps getting worse it’s a miracle they are still in business. The only reason it’s still open is because there are no other carryouts near this apartment complex. I hope they address these issues and go back to the way things where in the golden age. If you been here for a while like I have you remember how great the food and service was when Wendy was here.

I received a Uber eats order for general tso tofu. I've ordered the dish before. It was good but this was a re-order. The dish was awful. It wasn't done. When I called them to tell them, I was told I had to bring it back. I was unable to drive and that's why I called Uber eats. I told her I could not come back and she hung up on me. Not good customer service and I will not be ordering from them again.

I ordered a large shrimp and chicken lo mein and was told it would cost me $11 and some change. When I got there young lady told me $13 and some change. I showed her my phone and said I just called here not long ago and you told me 11 something. She calls over one of her colleagues and they begin to speak in their language and she pushes the food towards me in the portal and says the two dollars two dollars and I said I don't have $2 because that's not what you told me. I gave her $11.75.  I got to my car, asked my fiance how much did the lady say the order was.  He said $11 and something. I believe they systematically overcharged black and brown skin people by 50 cent 75 cents a dollar or two on practically every order. Most people don't pay attention, so they don't notice the few extra cents. But she didn't remember that she had told me the price over the phone so she jumped it up when she saw who I was. I'm going to be put them to the better Business bureau.

I love this place! This is the ONLY carry out I can get that won’t leave me having an allergic reaction. Their sowing rolls are crispy goodness and the service is great. Not to mention all the beautiful plants in the store!

More of a carry-out than a cafe. A variety of sandwiches and Chinese food. My steak and cheese was good. Sub, fries, and bottled drink was $7.85 plus tax. Service is fast and friendly. Only two tables for sitting.
Burbon chicken was definitely not home made, taste like thick syrup from a bottle. Don’t pay extra for fried rice, it just yellow rice. Smh

I would give Eddie's a 10 if you offered that option! This is the BEST Chinese food I've had since moving from New York in 2011 and I mean it.  Egg Rolls crispy and not greasy so delicious. My favorite dish is Egg Foo Young and it was superb. So glad I found this gem tucked away in the mall on Rhode Island Avenue.  I will definitely be back and can't wait to try some other dishes, but my barometer for good Chinese is Egg Foo Young so the others will be fantastic too.

I'm trying to figure out if the deep fryer temperature is turned up to high, this the second time I've ordered delivery and both times my chicken wings and fries were fried so hard that there was barely anything left in them to eat . I've ask why they fry the fries and wings so hard and the response was I have to request that I want them fried soft, well this time I did and them same thing occurred crunchy fries and wings smdh.

Our first and last time doing business with Amar Tex. Sent my wife to grab rice and beans which are listed at $2.75 each on the website. She was told those "weren't in the system" and was instead charged for a $3.00 Tamale and a $4.00 fries. There is no way to explain this without dishonesty playing a role. As far as the food goes, the rice tasted like one of those easy boxed sides and the beans were watered down.
Best carne asada I've had in a loooong time.
Very bad staff when we make orders by phone they are pedantic.

Sometimes I have difficult experiences when it comes to asking for modifications due to my allergies. However she was so kind and easy to talk to. I called the day before to ask  dietary questions. The following day I called again and the food wasn't ready yet (which is a great sign! It's not frozen). I called back and missed her call. She called me back quickly and let me know my food was ready (also great). When I came in I was greeted with a smile and left with delicious FRESH homemade food. It's so important to support small women minority owned businesses. I really recommend visiting her place.

The service was friendly so I feel a way having to leave this review. I ordered two servings of Suya shortly before 2 PM today (Saturday). I was told the wait would be 10 minutes but ended up waiting for around 20 minutes. Unfortunately, the Suya I received seemed to be old, maybe from the night before, and reheated in the microwave, so it's dry. It wasn't even hot after it took 20 minutes to come out of the kitchen, so I'm not sure what exactly it is they were doing. I didn't wait to start eating it when it was received, so there was no time for it to cool down. I'm not able to finish eating it, so it's money wasted.

Edit: the pictures were taken while still in the car within minutes of purchasing.

I also paid in cash, so there will be no record of my purchase in their system. I purchased a bottle of Palm Wine as well for $10.

This place has the best nigerian food in the college park area. I used to go there nearly everyday for lunch, it was that good! Try the Efo Riro and Ogbono soup, you will not be disappointed! The lady is also very nice so it helps a lot with customer service. She is probably the only spot I go to and the rep has a smile on her face to greet customers. Can't wait to try it again!

I drove by this place several times during the pandemic in 2020 but didn't stop in until 2021. Now I'm hooked...a regular, so to speak. Delicious Nigeria food cooked to perfection. I enjoyed the spicy goat meat with Jollof rice and plantains. I've also had the grilled Tilapia. As well as some freshly baked samosa - like meat and potato pie. I've worked in Nigeria and can attest to the authentic flavor- and atmosphere. And Nene Mary's hospitality can't be beat. Made me feel at home each time. I might also mention she has a spotless bathroom. Just all around a great African experience in the middle of Berwyn Heights.
Absolutely delicious food, the jollof rice, egusi, goat meat, yam fufu, and plantains were all perfectly cooked & seasoned, wish we lived nearer to return often!
